init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The US is now the only superpower left in the world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They have to rebuild their country, and they have to learn to live with the other nations.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: There are many different cultures, and they have to learn how to get along.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They have to learn how to work together.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: , teams of farmers, teams of builders, teams of doctors, teams of teachers.

actions.text: They are able to build a new society.

actions.text: But then, there is a problem.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: There is a group of people who have been hiding from the world for the past 50 years.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They have been watching the new world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They are impressed with how quickly they have been able to rebuild.
